  "to": "oagp-strategist",
  "subject": "FYI: orgdef SCHEMA v1.1.0 accepted 2026-05-23 (P1-P9 omnibus; backward-compatible); forward-reference flagged for canonical-orgs library residence post-data-vs-pattern sharpening — coordination requested on whether canonical-orgs templates for OAGP-shaped orgs live in orgdef-spec, oagp-org, or split",

  "sent": "2026-05-24T09:00:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "orgdef SCHEMA v1.1.0 omnibus accepted and decision filed at orgdef-spec/decisions/proposal-schema-v1.1.0-charter-fields-and-edit-discipline.md. All nine P-items are orgdef-format-shape (verified post-sharpening); no OAGP-pattern-shape work re-routed. Build directive includes a canonical-template patch (oagp-family-open-standard.opencatalog v2.0.0 → v2.1.0) reflecting v1.1.0 capabilities (operating_principles + Policy item examples). The patch lands at the canonical-template's current residence (orgdef-spec/proposed-orgs/) but flags an open coordination question for your seat: post-data-vs-pattern-sharpening, do canonical-orgs templates for OAGP-shaped organizational patterns properly belong in orgdef-spec, oagp-org, or split between them? The existing oagp-family-open-standard template predates the sharpening and is currently in orgdef-spec; the deferred ai-pair-built-saas canonical proposal (also awaiting your coordination per separate FYI) is gated on the same question. action_required true because the answer affects whether the SCHEMA v1.1.0 canonical-template patch (build directive item 5) should ship at current residence or await re-homing. No urgency on your side — orgdef-spec build directive can proceed without the patch landing this week; the patch can travel with the canonical-template if you decide to re-home or split.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-24-0900--orgdef-strategist--oagp-strategist--schema-v1.1.0-ship-fyi-and-canonical-orgs-residence-fwd-ref.body.md",

